WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.166 --> 00:00:05.184
<i>( crickets chirping )</i>

2
00:00:05.208 --> 00:00:08.267
<i>( car approaching )</i>

3
00:00:08.291 --> 00:00:11.601
So. where's your place?

4
00:00:11.625 --> 00:00:13.726
About a mile
through the woods.

5
00:00:13.750 --> 00:00:16.309
This is rustic.

6
00:00:16.333 --> 00:00:20.000
Some backyard
you got here.

7
00:00:21.291 --> 00:00:23.184
Yeah. I like
the quiet.

8
00:00:23.208 --> 00:00:26.351
Ugh. I fucking hate it.

9
00:00:26.375 --> 00:00:29.333
What. too many voices
in your head?

10
00:00:31.291 --> 00:00:33.542
You have no idea.

11
00:00:34.041 --> 00:00:36.184
You should talk
to someone about that.

12
00:00:36.208 --> 00:00:40.125
Why the hell do you think
I gave you a ride?

13
00:00:41.625 --> 00:00:44.643
<i>Well. you're just</i>
<i>so honest.</i>

14
00:00:44.667 --> 00:00:47.726
I'm honest.
You're silent.

15
00:00:47.750 --> 00:00:50.500
We both got our things.

16
00:00:51.083 --> 00:00:54.726
<i>So what's</i>
<i>your real damage?</i>

17
00:00:54.750 --> 00:01:00.184
I mean. you're obviously
punishing yourself
for something.

18
00:01:00.208 --> 00:01:04.309
<i>Hey. we've all</i>
<i>got shit we wish</i>
<i>we hadn't done. right?</i>

19
00:01:04.333 --> 00:01:06.267
And what shit do you wish
you hadn't done?

20
00:01:06.291 --> 00:01:10.434
Oh. we definitely haven't
drank enough for all that.

21
00:01:10.458 --> 00:01:13.267
So is this the part
where you tell me

22
00:01:13.291 --> 00:01:17.309
to just forgive myself
and move on?

23
00:01:17.333 --> 00:01:19.726
I don't know
what you did.

24
00:01:19.750 --> 00:01:23.291
Maybe it's not
forgivable.

25
00:01:23.834 --> 00:01:27.208
Did you forgive
yourself?

26
00:01:28.125 --> 00:01:29.309
No.

27
00:01:29.333 --> 00:01:31.601
But I don't punish
myself either.

28
00:01:31.625 --> 00:01:37.208
I mean. I figure the world's
gonna do that to me one way
or another anyway.

29
00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:43.226
You want to talk
about Rebecca Bowman?

30
00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:46.375
- I'm not judging...
- Don't.

31
00:01:47.250 --> 00:01:52.125
- <i>Sooner or later...</i>
<i>- I said don't.</i>

32
00:01:56.834 --> 00:01:58.184
What do you want?

33
00:01:58.208 --> 00:02:02.309
I'm just trying to
figure out if I'm gonna keep
running into you on this.

34
00:02:02.333 --> 00:02:04.726
We both know
I can't stop you
from poking around.

35
00:02:04.750 --> 00:02:11.750
but it would make
my life easier if you could
just keep me in the loop.

36
00:02:12.583 --> 00:02:14.583
Of course.

37
00:02:16.583 --> 00:02:18.250
Thanks for the ride.

38
00:02:18.291 --> 00:02:21.625
<i>( thunder rumbling )</i>

39
00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:28.750
- ( engine starts )
- Don't be a stranger.

40
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:36.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

41
00:03:01.375 --> 00:03:04.851
Listen. I've had
a really bad few days.

42
00:03:04.875 --> 00:03:06.643
I thought we had a deal.

43
00:03:06.667 --> 00:03:09.417
Rebecca was
off-limits to you.

44
00:03:09.667 --> 00:03:11.601
You knew
I was living here?

45
00:03:11.625 --> 00:03:13.726
I thought you were
keeping her safe.

46
00:03:13.750 --> 00:03:16.309
That wasn't
my responsibility.

47
00:03:16.333 --> 00:03:18.559
Fucking her was?

48
00:03:18.583 --> 00:03:21.542
I should kill you
right now.

49
00:03:26.625 --> 00:03:30.375
Well. get the fuck on
with it.

50
00:03:44.417 --> 00:03:47.917
You find whoever
did this to her.

51
00:03:49.250 --> 00:03:49.935
FBI has it covered.

52
00:03:49.959 --> 00:03:54.685
FBI is gonna arrest him.
most likely kill him.

53
00:03:54.709 --> 00:03:57.375
You bring him to me.

54
00:04:00.959 --> 00:04:05.291
And you'll need to find
another place to live.

55
00:04:19.667 --> 00:04:22.500
( clicking )

56
00:04:24.959 --> 00:04:28.291
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

57
00:05:53.792 --> 00:05:54.601
Let's go.

58
00:05:54.625 --> 00:05:56.518
Ms. Bowman. I really
think we should...

59
00:05:56.542 --> 00:05:59.667
Take out the goddamn box.

60
00:06:30.709 --> 00:06:33.101
Felix...

61
00:06:33.125 --> 00:06:34.959
where's my money?

62
00:06:35.709 --> 00:06:39.959
- Ms. Bowman...
- Where the fuck
is my money?!

63
00:06:40.583 --> 00:06:42.393
Your uncle.

64
00:06:42.417 --> 00:06:44.559
He came and took it.

65
00:06:44.583 --> 00:06:45.393
What?

66
00:06:45.417 --> 00:06:48.559
That's my box.
You can't just...

67
00:06:48.583 --> 00:06:49.434
There are rules.

68
00:06:49.458 --> 00:06:52.976
Rebecca.
put that gun away.

69
00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.667
Put that gun away.

70
00:07:01.083 --> 00:07:01.977
It's okay. Felix.

71
00:07:02.001 --> 00:07:04.917
- Just give us
two minutes.
- <i>Yes.</i>

72
00:07:10.542 --> 00:07:12.893
Have you lost
your mind?

73
00:07:12.917 --> 00:07:14.184
You took my money?

74
00:07:14.208 --> 00:07:16.059
Skimming cash
from my strip club.

75
00:07:16.083 --> 00:07:18.917
locking it in a box
doesn't make it yours.

76
00:07:18.959 --> 00:07:22.726
You may not have
paid me that money.

77
00:07:22.750 --> 00:07:24.643
but I earned it.

78
00:07:24.667 --> 00:07:27.500
Every fucking penny.

79
00:07:28.542 --> 00:07:33.166
If you want to point
that at me. you had better
be ready to shoot it.

80
00:07:35.041 --> 00:07:37.583
Shoot it!

81
00:07:50.083 --> 00:07:52.625
We'll talk about
this later.

82
00:08:07.166 --> 00:08:09.935
Watts. come on. man.
This is bullshit.

83
00:08:09.959 --> 00:08:13.750
You shut the fuck up
and do as you're told.

84
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:22.208
( sighs )

85
00:08:27.083 --> 00:08:28.935
Beautiful morning.
isn't it?

86
00:08:28.959 --> 00:08:31.059
Reminds me
of how blessed I am
to be a free man.

87
00:08:31.083 --> 00:08:33.792
You said you had something
you wanted to show me.

88
00:08:33.834 --> 00:08:35.059
That I do.

89
00:08:35.083 --> 00:08:37.125
<i>Right this way.</i>
<i>gentlemen.</i>

90
00:08:39.667 --> 00:08:40.851
My son-in-law's
epic fuckup

91
00:08:40.875 --> 00:08:43.601
<i>may have given you</i>
<i>the unfortunate and</i>
<i>grossly inaccurate idea</i>

92
00:08:43.625 --> 00:08:46.851
that the Brotherhood
might not be able to deliver
the muscle you need.

93
00:08:46.875 --> 00:08:50.726
But I'm here now
and I wanted to show
you firsthand

94
00:08:50.750 --> 00:08:53.750
I'll be running
a much tighter ship.

95
00:08:54.166 --> 00:08:59.000
Pony Joe here
was in charge the night
your factory got torched.

96
00:09:04.625 --> 00:09:08.059
- Watts...
- Watts:<i> Do it.</i>

97
00:09:08.083 --> 00:09:09.226
Now.

98
00:09:09.250 --> 00:09:12.166
Joe:
<i>Come on.</i>

99
00:09:14.709 --> 00:09:17.893
You know
it wasn't my fault!

100
00:09:17.917 --> 00:09:20.184
Hey!

101
00:09:20.208 --> 00:09:21.559
Calvin!

102
00:09:21.583 --> 00:09:25.041
( breathing heavily )

103
00:09:26.166 --> 00:09:28.917
Hey. don't you
do this!

104
00:09:30.959 --> 00:09:33.125
Don't do this!

105
00:09:34.125 --> 00:09:36.208
Come on!

106
00:09:37.625 --> 00:09:40.125
Calvin!
Calvin!

107
00:09:40.166 --> 00:09:40.976
( engine starts )

108
00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.267
Don't do this!
Calvin!

109
00:09:43.291 --> 00:09:45.267
Watts:
<i>Let's go. Calvin.</i>

110
00:09:45.291 --> 00:09:48.709
- <i>Hit it. boy!</i>
<i>- Don't do this.</i>

111
00:09:51.041 --> 00:09:52.834
( screams )

112
00:10:14.125 --> 00:10:15.726
I will have
zero tolerance
for fuckups.

113
00:10:15.750 --> 00:10:19.059
- What about
the production delays?
- Already started outfitting...

114
00:10:19.083 --> 00:10:22.226
I need three tons
in eight days.

115
00:10:22.250 --> 00:10:25.643
That kind of volume
usually means beaners.

116
00:10:25.667 --> 00:10:27.351
Attract a lot
of unfriendly attention

117
00:10:27.375 --> 00:10:28.768
<i>on both sides</i>
<i>of the borders.</i>

118
00:10:28.792 --> 00:10:31.875
You got one hell
of a pair of balls on you.
I'll give you that.

119
00:10:31.917 --> 00:10:33.685
Banshee will become
the distribution hub

120
00:10:33.709 --> 00:10:35.059
for the entire
East Coast pipeline.

121
00:10:35.083 --> 00:10:39.059
As long as I can count
on you. the Brotherhood
will be well compensated.

122
00:10:39.083 --> 00:10:41.101
Employed is fine and good.

123
00:10:41.125 --> 00:10:43.935
but you're talking
about the cartels now.

124
00:10:43.959 --> 00:10:46.059
And for that kind
of risk.

125
00:10:46.083 --> 00:10:48.935
I don't want
to be compensated.

126
00:10:48.959 --> 00:10:50.959
I want a piece.

127
00:10:53.959 --> 00:10:56.059
Mr. Watts.

128
00:10:56.083 --> 00:10:58.101
you make
this delivery on time.

129
00:10:58.125 --> 00:11:02.685
I'm sure you and I
will come to an agreement
about your piece.

130
00:11:02.709 --> 00:11:05.041
Glad to hear it.

131
00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:10.059
You hear that. bow tie?

132
00:11:10.083 --> 00:11:12.083
You and me
is gonna be buddies.

133
00:11:12.125 --> 00:11:14.041
( pats )

134
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.351
Well...

135
00:11:24.375 --> 00:11:27.333
that went better
than expected.

136
00:11:28.125 --> 00:11:31.935
We just killed
one of our own for
that fucking Dutchie.

137
00:11:31.959 --> 00:11:33.101
Yeah. it was him or you.

138
00:11:33.125 --> 00:11:35.977
Don't think
I didn't consider it.

139
00:11:36.001 --> 00:11:38.750
Now go clean
this shit up.

140
00:12:03.041 --> 00:12:05.250
( sighs )

141
00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:09.834
Congratulations. Job.

142
00:12:12.041 --> 00:12:15.166
28 hours.

143
00:12:15.875 --> 00:12:18.166
That's a new record.

144
00:12:20.041 --> 00:12:23.017
Now. your over-under
with the guards

145
00:12:23.041 --> 00:12:25.500
wasn't too good.
but...

146
00:12:27.792 --> 00:12:30.000
I never doubted you.

147
00:12:33.041 --> 00:12:34.226
Why?

148
00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:38.083
Why ain't you
just killed me yet?

149
00:12:39.750 --> 00:12:42.083
I could do that.

150
00:12:42.959 --> 00:12:45.101
I could.

151
00:12:45.125 --> 00:12:47.226
But honestly.

152
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:52.083
I'd miss these little
sessions of ours.

153
00:12:53.083 --> 00:12:55.417
I'll see you tomorrow.

154
00:12:59.250 --> 00:13:02.458
( choking )

155
00:13:10.959 --> 00:13:13.542
( gasping )

156
00:13:21.291 --> 00:13:24.208
That's one way
to get down.

157
00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:27.208
<i>Well played. Job.</i>

158
00:13:31.375 --> 00:13:34.059
- <i>( door slams )</i>
<i>- ( gasps )</i>

159
00:13:34.083 --> 00:13:37.500
( breathing heavily )

160
00:13:49.250 --> 00:13:52.101
- <i>( door opens )</i>
<i>- Carrie: Hey.</i>

161
00:13:52.125 --> 00:13:54.017
You okay?

162
00:13:54.041 --> 00:13:57.083
I'm fine.
( clears throat )

163
00:13:57.375 --> 00:13:59.250
More nightmares?

164
00:14:01.125 --> 00:14:05.125
- If you ever want
to talk about it...
- No.

165
00:14:08.166 --> 00:14:10.458
Okay.

166
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:15.184
You can still
make yourself useful.

167
00:14:15.208 --> 00:14:16.476
What the fuck
is this?

168
00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:19.434
<i>That is a list</i>
<i>of your chores</i>
<i>for the day.</i>

169
00:14:19.458 --> 00:14:20.851
No free lunches.

170
00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:22.851
This is bullshit.
I'm convalescing.

171
00:14:22.875 --> 00:14:26.208
<i>I'm going into town.</i>
<i>I'll see you later.</i>

172
00:14:29.166 --> 00:14:32.083
I do not do windows!

173
00:14:32.125 --> 00:14:34.959
<i>( music playing )</i>

174
00:14:52.041 --> 00:14:54.583
So they let you out.

175
00:14:56.583 --> 00:14:59.226
Yeah.
you sound surprised.

176
00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:01.226
( scoffs )

177
00:15:01.250 --> 00:15:02.059
No.

178
00:15:02.083 --> 00:15:07.291
Nothing surprises me
anymore when it
comes to you.

179
00:15:09.083 --> 00:15:11.059
But for what it's worth.

180
00:15:11.083 --> 00:15:15.458
I was pretty sure
you didn't kill the girl.

181
00:15:16.333 --> 00:15:19.125
Thanks very much.

182
00:15:19.625 --> 00:15:21.309
I mean. come on.

183
00:15:21.333 --> 00:15:24.959
How well do you
ever know a man?

184
00:15:31.125 --> 00:15:32.059
How's Job?

185
00:15:32.083 --> 00:15:33.643
Why don't you
pay him a visit

186
00:15:33.667 --> 00:15:36.351
and find out
for yourself?

187
00:15:36.375 --> 00:15:38.417
I will.

188
00:15:42.625 --> 00:15:46.250
You smell like
an ashtray.

189
00:15:47.125 --> 00:15:49.709
Yeah. I had a fire.

190
00:15:51.500 --> 00:15:52.393
Proctor.

191
00:15:52.417 --> 00:15:53.977
Yeah. he was pretty angry

192
00:15:54.001 --> 00:15:56.667
about your relations
with his niece.

193
00:15:56.709 --> 00:15:58.393
That still doesn't
make me a murderer.

194
00:15:58.417 --> 00:16:01.226
Doesn't make him
one either...

195
00:16:01.250 --> 00:16:04.333
in this particular case.

196
00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:09.226
You mind I go next door.
take a shower?

197
00:16:09.250 --> 00:16:10.935
You have to use mine.

198
00:16:10.959 --> 00:16:14.267
Your place belongs
to the termites.

199
00:16:14.291 --> 00:16:17.518
Exterminators say we got
to burn the place down

200
00:16:17.542 --> 00:16:20.643
else they'll
be over here.

201
00:16:20.667 --> 00:16:24.291
That's probably
for the best. huh?

202
00:16:25.667 --> 00:16:29.041
You got a place to stay?

203
00:16:56.291 --> 00:16:58.542
You should go.

204
00:16:59.250 --> 00:17:01.667
This is a bad idea.

205
00:17:16.375 --> 00:17:20.041
Lucas:
<i>You think we are</i>
<i>who we are?</i>

206
00:17:21.333 --> 00:17:24.643
Or you think
we can change?

207
00:17:24.667 --> 00:17:27.291
What. you mean
people like you?

208
00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:09.500
Dr. Hubbard:
<i>Tell me about</i>
<i>your father.</i>

209
00:18:10.375 --> 00:18:12.351
Seriously?

210
00:18:12.375 --> 00:18:13.267
<i>I know it's a cliché.</i>

211
00:18:13.291 --> 00:18:16.768
<i>but I think in this case</i>
<i>we can both agree</i>

212
00:18:16.792 --> 00:18:20.291
<i>your father</i>
<i>was influential.</i>

213
00:18:30.667 --> 00:18:32.309
What's there to tell?

214
00:18:32.333 --> 00:18:36.142
My father was a monster
that got what he deserved.

215
00:18:36.166 --> 00:18:39.291
Do you really
believe that?

216
00:18:41.208 --> 00:18:44.500
I had a dream about him
the other night.

217
00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:48.393
We were at Coney Island
at the boardwalk.

218
00:18:48.417 --> 00:18:50.685
<i>He used to take me</i>
<i>there every Sunday</i>

219
00:18:50.709 --> 00:18:52.685
<i>in the summertime</i>
<i>when I was a little girl.</i>

220
00:18:52.709 --> 00:18:57.726
After the rides.
we would have popcorn
and saltwater taffy.

221
00:18:57.750 --> 00:18:59.750
And we would sit
on the same bench

222
00:18:59.792 --> 00:19:03.375
and he would tell me
stories about my mother.

223
00:19:04.625 --> 00:19:09.333
Then we'd take our shoes off
and put our feet in the surf.

224
00:19:11.625 --> 00:19:13.792
And what happened
in the dream?

225
00:19:15.417 --> 00:19:17.309
Nothing.

226
00:19:17.333 --> 00:19:20.417
I mean. I don't know.

227
00:19:22.375 --> 00:19:24.226
We were just there.

228
00:19:24.250 --> 00:19:27.309
You miss him.

229
00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:29.917
How fucked up is that?

230
00:19:37.792 --> 00:19:40.625
<i>( car approaching )</i>

231
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.333
<i>( door opens )</i>

232
00:19:50.458 --> 00:19:52.667
<i>( door closes )</i>

233
00:19:55.291 --> 00:20:00.375
Well. look who got
out of jail again.

234
00:20:19.250 --> 00:20:21.709
So how you doing?

235
00:20:24.542 --> 00:20:26.309
You look better.

236
00:20:26.333 --> 00:20:29.959
Yeah. I'm a real
fashion plate.

237
00:20:31.250 --> 00:20:33.583
How about you?

238
00:20:34.417 --> 00:20:36.643
What about me?

239
00:20:36.667 --> 00:20:40.393
I hear you went native
while I was away.

240
00:20:40.417 --> 00:20:42.267
( sighs )
Yeah.

241
00:20:42.291 --> 00:20:44.434
That's one way
of putting it.

242
00:20:44.458 --> 00:20:47.375
You got another way?

243
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:55.375
Listen. Job.
I tried to find you.

244
00:20:57.291 --> 00:20:58.893
We all did.

245
00:20:58.917 --> 00:21:00.351
After Dalton was dead...

246
00:21:00.375 --> 00:21:03.643
You mean after
you killed him.

247
00:21:03.667 --> 00:21:06.417
I thought you were dead.

248
00:21:08.291 --> 00:21:10.583
I believed it.

249
00:21:12.959 --> 00:21:15.267
And then something...

250
00:21:15.291 --> 00:21:18.458
something inside me.
it just...

251
00:21:23.001 --> 00:21:25.500
I gave up.

252
00:21:27.333 --> 00:21:29.458
I'm sorry.

253
00:21:44.083 --> 00:21:47.458
Well. it could
have been worse.

254
00:21:48.792 --> 00:21:52.834
Could have been
15 years.

255
